{
  "stem": "12462.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I hadn't particularly gotten to know him well.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But when I was in Nuremberg, he came over as an assistant to Justice Jackson sometime before the trial.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he immediately grabbed a hold of me and said, I need this, I need that, and so on.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And although he was not my boss, I managed to work on the side.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My boss was Colonel Storey, the head of the Documentation Division.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I did all this work for him, including getting translations of all the oaths which different branches of the Nazi organization had, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But he got into a squabble with Justice Jackson.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He was preferring to hold-- have a lot of witnesses and to have some plea bargaining with some of the defendants, possible defendants, and Justice Jackson was entirely against this.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So they had a break-up, and Justice-- General Donovan just left Nuremberg, and he didn't even say good-bye.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think he stayed until about the end of the first week of trial.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And at that time, Jackson told him that he would not allow him to cross-examine witnesses or to have witnesses, because of this dispute they had as to-- to the various things.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it was just two great minds and two people of great stature not being able to-- to get along together.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I knew that there was discrimination, and I knew that, of course, that Jews were being sent into the East.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
